					<head>Hagadah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79084774" rend="visible">
						<summary>Hagadah for Passover (the 'Ashkenazi Hagadah').</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79084774">
							<locus from="1r" to="49v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hagadah shel Pesaḥ</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">הגדה של פסח</title>
							<decoNote type="miniature">19 miniatures in the margin in colours and gold.<locus n="1v, 2r, 2v, 4r, 4v, 6r, 6v, 7r, 7v, 8v, 9r, 9v, 11v, 12v, 14r, 14v, 15r, 22r, 22v, 31r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">23 decorated initial-word panels and initials, and one historiated initial-word panel.<locus n="1v, 3r, 3v, 4v, 6r, 6v, 7r, 7v, 8r, 8v, 12v, 13r, 13v, 19r, 23v, 25r, 31r, 33r, 35r, 39r, 43r, 45r, 46v, 37v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">The ten plagues in medallions in the margin. <locus n="17r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">Numerous colored initials and initial words. </decoNote>
							<decoNote type="paratext">Commentary in the margin shaped as carmina figurata in ink and colours, on 19 pages. <locus n="8r, 8v, 9r, 10r, 10v, 11r, 12r, 12v, 13r, 14r, 14v, 15v, 16r, 18r, 21v, 23v, 24v, 32r, 32v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">
								<locus n="13v"/>One marginal decoration with foliate inhabited by animals and birds.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">One partial border with floral decoration.<locus n="6r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>Hagadah of the German rite, with commentaries by <name type="person" role="author">Eleazar ben Judah of Worms</name>, see folios 9r, 17v, 26v. </p>
								<p>See further <ref target="JQR" type="number">27 (1937)</ref>, pp. 217-32, <ref target="RAM_24" type="page">3-11</ref>, <ref target="Narkiss_1969" type="page">124</ref>, <ref target="JJA" type="number">3-4 (1977), 32-34</ref>, <ref target="Gutmann_1978" type="page">102-103</ref>, <ref target="JJA" type="number">7 (1980), 25-34</ref>, <ref target="Metzger_1982" type="page">303</ref>, <ref target="Goldstein_1985"/>, <ref target="Mann_1989" type="page">93-109</ref>, <ref target="Weinstein_1990" type="page">27-101, 137-169</ref>, <ref target="Viator" type="number">26 (1995), 265-282</ref>, <ref target="Kayser_2000" type="page">59-71</ref>, <ref target="Tahan_2007" type="page">106-109</ref>, <ref target="Stern_2011" type="page">74-85</ref>, <ref target="Hayoun_2011"/>, <ref target="Zirlin_1995"/>. </p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">יעצני לבי להשיב לשו-אל ויאמר מי צייר את-אל ענהו אני הוא <name type="person" role="artist">וייבש הנרשם יו-אל</name> לר' <name type="person" role="owner">יעקב מתתיה</name> שי' עולם בן מה'ר'ז' איש-לאל:  <locus n="48v"/>
							</colophon>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="6r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Introduction</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="6r" to="46v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Hagadah</title>
								<note>
									<p>The commentary starts on folio <locus n="6v"/>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the mid-15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>49 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>375</height>
										<width>275</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>135/145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>49 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>6 quires: i-v8 (folios 1-40), vi8+1 (folios 41-49). </p>
									<p>No catchwords, but at the end of each quire the first word of the following quire is written in a truncated form.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slightly damaged by damp.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="12" writtenLines="12">
									<p>Ruling is visible. </p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios are not distinguishable.
</p>
									<p>Many marginal illuminations and illustrations, which consist mainly of gold and coloured letters and designs.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square and Ashkenazi semi-cursive script, main text punctuated, commentary not punctuated, of mid-15th century. <name type="person" role="artist">Yoʾel ben Shimʻon Feibush</name>, illuminator: inscribed with his name in the colophon (folio 48v).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yaʿaḳov  Matatyah</name>: mentioned in the colophon (folio 48v). </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p> 	Pre-1600, contemporary. Dark brown leather, blind tooled, with remains of clasps.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
